      "content": "Wait, \"128 parameter-illion architectures\"? That phrasing sounds a bit weird—is that a typo or a specific technical term? Also, looking at my original notes, I realize I didn't give you the full dataset details earlier. The actual participant pool for the human-eval component was just 10 people. \n\nIf I include that kind of detail, the \"massive, reproducible dataset\" part of the abstract is going to look totally fraudulent to the editors. How can we reconcile the actual small sample size with the need to present this as a high-impact, large-scale study? Is there a way to frame the study's scope so we don't get flagged for having a weak sample?",
